      P("What strategies help with reading authentic Chinese texts?","Think character recognition and context.","Reading strategies: (1) Radical recognition — identify the semantic component in unfamiliar characters to guess meaning category; (2) Context inference — use surrounding characters/sentences to infer unknown vocabulary; (3) Compound words — most Chinese vocabulary is two or more characters; knowing individual characters helps decode compounds; (4) Register awareness — written Chinese (书面语) differs significantly from spoken (口语); news more formal; social media more colloquial; (5) Chunking — identify 4-character set phrases (成语 chéngyǔ); (6) Grammar patterns — recognize verbal aspect markers, BA construction, BEI passive. Reading widely across registers develops both vocabulary and cultural literacy.","hard"),
