      P("How do you write a formal email or letter in Chinese?","Think register and structure.","Formal Chinese letter/email: Opening: address with title and name (尊敬的XX老师); purpose statement early. Body: clear paragraph structure; formal vocabulary (请, 恳请 for requests rather than 我要); complete sentences; appropriate verb aspects and particles. Closing: polite formulaic closing (此致/敬礼 for letters; 期待您的回复 'looking forward to your reply'); your name and date. Register: formal written Chinese avoids contractions, colloquialisms; uses complete subject-verb-object sentences; no 呢/吗 question particles (use declarative + 吗? only in less formal); appropriate measure words and particles throughout. AP Writing: demonstrate range of vocabulary and grammatical structures; address prompt specifically.","medium"),
