      P("How do you give an effective presentation in Chinese?","Think organization and vocabulary range.","Presentation strategies: (1) Introduction — state topic and main points (今天我要讲的是...); (2) Clear organization — use transition phrases (首先...其次...最后... first, then, finally); (3) Vocabulary range — demonstrate both formal vocabulary and nuanced vocabulary; use chéngyǔ (成语 four-character idioms) appropriately; (4) Specific examples and evidence — rather than vague statements; (5) Cultural connection — connect topic to Chinese cultural context when relevant; (6) Conclusion — summary + personal stance (我认为/总的来说); (7) Register maintenance — formal presentational context requires avoiding colloquial fillers. Pronunciation: tone accuracy, not perfection — clear communication prioritized.","medium"),
